Makes predictions with a trained PyTorch model.

Makes predictions with a trained scratch Adjacent Category model.

Makes predictions with a trained CORAL model.

dl_trainer.predict_pom_scratch(model, X_test)¶

Makes predictions with a trained scratch POM model.

Handles the training loop for the scratch Adjacent Category model.

Handles the training loop for a CORAL model.

Module for evaluating machine learning models on various datasets.

evaluate.main()¶

Main function to parse arguments, evaluate models, and save results.

This function sets up argument parsing for dataset, model types (scikit-learn or PyTorch), loads the specified dataset, and performs 30 runs of training and evaluation. It calculates various metrics, aggregates them, and saves the results to a JSON file.

Module for generating LaTeX tables from model evaluation results.

generate_table.generate_latex_table(df, model_order)¶

Generates a LaTeX table from a DataFrame with mean/std results and significance.

Parameters:

  • df (pandas.DataFrame) – DataFrame containing model performance data.

  • model_order (list) – A list of model names in the desired display order.

Returns:

A string containing the complete LaTeX table.

Return type:

str

Utility functions for data loading, preprocessing, and metric calculation.

util.calculate_metrics(y_true, y_pred, is_regression=False)¶

Calculates and returns a dictionary of evaluation metrics.

For regression tasks, it computes Mean Absolute Error (MAE) and Mean Squared Error (MSE). For classification tasks, it computes MAE, Quadratic Weighted Kappa (QWK), MSE, Accuracy, and Adjusted Balanced Accuracy.

Parameters:

  • y_true (array-like) – True labels or target values.

  • y_pred (array-like) – Predicted labels or target values.

  • is_regression (bool, optional) – If True, calculates regression metrics. If False, calculates classification metrics.

Returns:

A dictionary where keys are metric names and values are their computed scores.

Return type:

dict

util.get_serializable_params(model)¶

Gets JSON-serializable parameters from a scikit-learn model.

Iterates through a scikit-learn model’s parameters and converts non-serializable types (like objects or functions) to their string representations, making the dictionary suitable for JSON serialization.

Parameters:

model – A fitted scikit-learn model instance.

Returns:

A dictionary of serializable model parameters.

Return type:

dict

util.load_boston_housing()¶

Loads the Boston Housing dataset and converts it to an ordinal problem.

The continuous ‘MEDV’ target is converted into 4 ordinal categories using quartiles. Features are then scaled.

Returns:

A tuple containing: - X (pd.DataFrame): Features DataFrame. - y (pd.Series): Ordinal target Series. - is_regression (bool): False, as it’s now a classification problem.

Return type:

tuple

util.load_car_evaluation()¶

Loads and preprocesses the Car Evaluation dataset.

Applies ordinal encoding to categorical features and the target variable.

Returns:

A tuple containing: - X (pd.DataFrame): Features DataFrame. - y (pd.Series): Target Series. - is_regression (bool): False, as it’s a classification problem.

Return type:

tuple

util.load_dataset(name)¶

Dispatcher to load the specified dataset.

Parameters:

name (str) – The name of the dataset to load (e.g., ‘car’, ‘wine’, ‘boston’, ‘poker’).

Returns:

A tuple containing: - X (pd.DataFrame): Features DataFrame. - y (pd.Series): Target Series. - is_regression (bool): True if regression, False if classification.

Return type:

tuple

Raises:

ValueError – If an unknown dataset name is provided.

util.load_poker_hand()¶

Loads and preprocesses the Poker Hand dataset.

Remaps target labels to be zero-indexed.

Returns:

A tuple containing: - X (pd.DataFrame): Features DataFrame. - y (pd.Series): Target Series (zero-indexed). - is_regression (bool): False, as it’s a classification problem.

Return type:

tuple

util.load_wine_quality()¶

Loads and preprocesses the Wine Quality dataset.

Combines red and white wine datasets, then scales numerical features.

Returns:

A tuple containing: - X (pd.DataFrame): Features DataFrame. - y (pd.Series): Target Series. - is_regression (bool): False, as it’s a classification problem.

Return type:

tuple
